Mexico

In  Mexico, clients have access to a complete suite of corporate and investment banking  products and services. Through our offices located in Mexico City, Monterrey,  and Guadalajara, Scotiabank's Global Banking and Markets division operates  through teams of relationship managers and product specialists working together  to offer multi-product solutions to clients' financial needs. We provide a full  range of corporate and investment banking and capital markets products and  services such as lending, debt and equity financing, mergers and acquisitions, risk management, securitization, trading, and foreign exchange. We also provide access to cash management, trade  finance, and various research products.




  



  In Mexico, we are organized by industry specialty groups, with industry experts  supported by product specialists to best serve the specific requirements of our  clients. This enables us to be expert in both an individual company's needs, as  well as the industry in which it operates. In Mexico, we have the following  industry specializations: 

Automotive
Infrastructure
Public Sector
Mining
Real Estate
Regional Diversified  Industries
Retail
Telecommunications  and Media


The Diversified Industries  Group services clients within their geographic region, across a wide range of  industries. Also included in this Group are our European Companies specialists. 




We offer full-service corporate and investment banking and capital markets  product capabilities offered through the following departments: 
Corporate and Investment Banking
The Corporate and  Investment Banking group in Mexico includes traditional services such as  corporate and investment products, corporate lending and loan syndications,  equity and debt underwriting, and mergers and acquisitions. All product  specialists within this group work together as a team to deliver integrated  solutions to clients' needs that best match their needs and capitalize on  opportunities available to them. These product specialists also work across a  number of industries to deliver specialized knowledge of the industry context  in which a given company operates. 
Global Equity Sales and Trading
The Global Equity Sales and  Trading group in Mexico represents an integrated area dealing with debt and  equity capital markets, sales and trading services, and institutional sales.  Our traders have built solid relationships with the institutional buy-side  through a professional approach and understanding each client's portfolio and  trading style. The trading desk offers a full-service approach, from idea  generation to execution. 
Foreign Exchange
In Mexico, our Foreign  Exchange group is responsible for clients' monetary exchange needs in the  Mexican market, as well as managing foreign exchange risk exposure for clients.  The group coordinates local coverage with our global FX team headquartered in  Toronto to provide outstanding service and innovative products to clients in  Mexico. 
Derivatives Sales
In Mexico, our  Derivatives group provides innovative investment and risk management solutions.  According to a client's risk profile, we design protection from fluctuating  exchange and interest rates, as well as from market risk, through various  hedging strategies. Our products and services include interest rate swaps, cross-currency  interest rate swaps, exchange rate futures, forwards and options, future rate  agreements, interest rate options (caps, floors, collars), derivatives listed  on the Mexican Derivatives Market, futures and options on stocks and indices,  as well as advice to manage and diversify risks. 




  Through other areas of Scotiabank, clients in Mexico also have access to a full  range of Cash Management, Trade Finance and Correspondent Banking, Trust  Services, and Treasury Services.



  Our ability to also service clients in Canada and the U.S. allows us to provide  total NAFTA coverage for corporate, institutional and government clients, both  domestic and local affiliates of multi-national companies. 


Ways to contact  us




  To find out more about Scotiabank  products and services available in Mexico, please contact:

