Brazil

Scotiabank has operated in  Brazil with a representative office since the early 1970's providing trade  finance and correspondent banking services through affiliates abroad. In 2008,  we expanded our global infrastructure finance platform in Brazil, and in  September 2011, after completing an acquisition, Scotiabank is operating a  fully licensed bank, offering clients access to a wide range of corporate and  investment banking and capital markets products and services.



      



      With more than 30,000 employees based in Latin America, we also have a large  presence in other Latin American countries, including Chile, Colombia, Mexico  and Peru.



        



        In Brazil, clients have access to the following products and services: 
Corporate Banking  (Large and Middle Market)

Asset based Loans 
Discounting of Receivables 
Equipment Finance 
Infrastructure Related Loans 
Inventory Finance 
Portfolio Purchases 
Syndicated and Leveraged Loans 
Term Loans 
Trade Related Finance 
Working Capital 


