Investor Solutions
Scotia Managed Companies




 



Scotiabank’s Commodity  Derivatives group is a trading and sales platform  that delivers financial and risk-management solutions to producers and  consumers of energy and agricultural products. Our  truly integrated energy platform unites origination and structuring, trading,  financing, and research.
We help clients  manage their exposure to the risk of fluctuating prices of energy and other  commodities through the development and implementation of effective customized  financial hedging strategies. The team’s expertise encompasses a full range of energy  and related products, including crude oil, refined products, natural gas, electric  power and emissions, among many other commodities. With trading capabilities  for products across North America, Latin America and Europe, we are  exceptionally well positioned to provide hedging solutions to our clients. Our  clients benefit from our detailed knowledge of the commodity markets and a  full-service product suite, from vanilla hedging to structured financing  solutions, including inventory finance. Through our sales teams, we are well positioned to leverage our tremendous energy  footprint in the region. 
 Our product capabilities  include:
Derivative  Products 

Commodity Swaps
Commodity Options 
Commodity Collars
Customized Structures

Financing

Inventory Finance
Investor Solutions 
 Bespoke  Solutions

Our teams offer:        

Origination  and Structuring 

With our extensive knowledge of  energy and related markets, we develop innovative and competitive hedging  structures.

Trading   

We provide competitive market  quotes on futures, forwards, swaps, options, swaptions, calendar spreads and  basis swaps.
We  provide advice on energy and related markets with a focus on crude oil and  refined products, natural gas, and electric power. 

Financing   

We provide structured financing  to commodity producers and end users.

Research

Our research team publishes  market updates with market insight and pricing.
We provide in-depth research and  analysis on domestic and international markets.






Contacts
For more  information on how our solutions can work for you, please  contact:
Energy Commodities

