Company Overview of Scotia Capital (USA) Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Scotia Capital (USA) Inc. offers investment banking services including securities underwriting and brokerage. It also provides corporate lending, economic research, fund management, mergers and acquisitions as well as money market services, and structured finance and leasing. The company’s clientele base covers industry groups such as communications, media, and technology; financial services and real estate; forest products; power, oil and gas, and pipelines; and mining among others. Scotia Capital (USA) Inc. was founded in 1939 and is based in New York with additional offices in California, Oregon, Texas, Massachusetts, and Georgia. Scotia Capital (USA) Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Scot...
Scotia Capital (USA) Inc. offers investment banking services including securities underwriting and brokerage. It also provides corporate lending, economic research, fund management, mergers and acquisitions as well as money market services, and structured finance and leasing. The company’s clientele base covers industry groups such as communications, media, and technology; financial services and real estate; forest products; power, oil and gas, and pipelines; and mining among others. Scotia Capital (USA) Inc. was founded in 1939 and is based in New York with additional offices in California, Oregon, Texas, Massachusetts, and Georgia. Scotia Capital (USA) Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Scotia Holdings (US) Inc. and BNS Investments Inc.
